latestPosts.caption:
New Cover with @sobhitad @vogueindia 
Besides sharing a native tongue and a career in film, Sobhita Dhulipala and Naga Chaitanya Akkineni had little in common. But that didn’t get in the way of their love story, “It just happened very organically,” says Dhulipala. In their first interview post-marriage for Vogue’s April digital cover, the couple reveal how their long-distance romance makes the little things count—eating meals with family, finding pockets of time to do nothing together and chatting in Telugu. “We’ve chalked out the next four or five months based on her commitments and mine, but we’re always looking for time to squeeze in a holiday or chill together,” says Akkineni. Read the full April digital cover story at the link in bio.
